==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kuz-'', from Indo-European ''*geus-'' ‘taste, choose’.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''kiāsa'', Old Saxon [[kiosan]] (Dutch [[kiezen]]), Old High German [[kiosan]], Old Norse ''kjósa'', Gothic [[𐌺𐌹𐌿𐍃𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root was also the source of Latin [[gustare]] ‘to taste’, Albanian [[desha]] ‘chosen’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʧe:ozan/

